observations.recommendation:
In view of the foregoing, we recommended that the Local Chief Executive, strictly:
a) To give justification and reliability to the amount of the account PPE on all funds;
b) Mandate the Inventory Committee to conduct an annual detailed physical count of all PPEs as of a specific date and submit the RPCPPE to the audit team not later than January 31, of each year.
c) General Services Officer shall maintain and update his property cards per category of property, plant and equipment, pursuant to Section 119 of MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I;
d) Municipal Accountant shall maintain and update his property ledger cards per category of property, plant and equipment, pursuant to Section 120 of MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I;
e) Ensure that the General Services Office and Municipal Accountant shall reconcile their property cards and property ledger cards, respectively; and

We recommended the Management to:
a. Instruct the GSO to keep and maintain Stock Cards for each and every supply to have an adequate monitoring and immediate information of supplies on hand;
b. Require the Accounting Division to keep and maintain Supplies Ledger Cards to record supplies received, issued and the balance both in quantity and amount;
c. Ensure proper coordination between GSO and Accounting Division to have an updated and reconciled balances in their Stock Cards and Supplies Ledger Cards, respectively; and
d. Prepare and submit the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) for Calendar Year 2021, in compliance with Section 121 of the Manual on the New Government Accounting System for Local Government Units, Volume I.
